	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Jan 30th 12:08 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2> I have a level 19 monk which I recently brought out of retirement.&nbsp;&nbsp;If you check out the Monkly Business web site you will see that at level 19 my fist are 7 damage / 36 delay weapons.  Given that max damage is 7+1+(level/2) that means my max damage is 17 (rounded down) every 3.6 seconds per hand (lets assume I am having a really good battle and always hit for max with both hands on every attack).  <br><br>I have acquired a pair of Polished Steel Ulaks (no twink, I got lucky and found them on a vendor for 5pp each).  Damage is 8 and delay is 28. So, now my max damage is 18 per 2.8 seconds. So, my damage output per hand increases from 4.72 hits/sec to 6.43 hits/second with each hand.<br><br>So, if you want to know if a weapon is worth using keep in mind that your empty hand to hand damage/delay ratio needs to be compared against the weapon's damage delay ratio.  Remember that STR bonuses only apply to primary hand so a weapon may actually be better for your off hand but not better for your primary. <br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
