<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=101217743431463></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101217743431463><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=3&mid=101217743431463>RE: New Monk</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=3&mid=101217743431463#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=118989><span id=Sage>Superchum</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>72 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Jan 27th 8:25 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Greetings brother monk. Congratulations on getting the Ulak. It's a wonderful weapon at lower levels.<br><br>To answer your questions:<br><br>Work on 2hb, 1hb and h2h a LOT. Keep those combat skill maxxed.<br><br>Round kick loses its usefulness after you get Tiger Claw, which loses its usefulness after you get Eagle Strike.<br><br>Dragon Punch and Flying Kick are the most superior special attacks you get. But Eagle Strike is used in your 60th level discipline, so you may want to keep that trained.<br><br>Trade Skills? For a monk? Whatever works. I'd say jewelry isn't your forte, but hey, if you KNOW an enchanter, you can do it. Other than that, it's whatever you can do and like doing. A LOT of monks like to tailor, but don't be fooled. By the time you CAN tailor Wu's armor, you'll have long outgrown it. It's an expensive trade and is hard to raise up without massive amounts of time invested. If you want to tailor, you can. But don't expect to actually be tailoring your own armor unless you spend an inordinate amount of money or time to train the skill early on.<br><br>As far as gear and overall costs go, depends on the monk. The weapons, I've found to be much more expensive than MOST of the armor you're going to want to wear. But even the weapons are cheap compared to other classes' weapons. That being said, A Fungus Covered Scale Tunic is STILL a Fungus Covered Scale Tunic. The Cloak of Flames is NOT cheap. Tranquil Staff isn't bargain basement 2hb. Trannix Crown's price is nothing to sneeze at.<br><br>There are always going to be way overpriced or way overpowerful gear no matter the class.<br><br>-Wubao<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br>"Mental gives the signal to the physical ... whirlwind kicks and hits from every angle."</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
