	   <tr><td colspan=2>Last I heard chance to hit was a formula related to both AC and ATK ... basically the mob's attack minus your ac give you a number on a data table which determines how often you get hit and what sort of damage mitigation is involved. (Which is why Gnoll Pups can't really hit you much anymore at level 40 for example ... their attack rating is so low).<br><br>I just always figured the SAME set of calculations were involved in YOU hitting the MOB as well.<br><br>-Wubao<br>&nbsp;<br>"Mental gives the signal to the physical ... whirlwind kicks and hits from every angle."</td></tr>
