	   <tr><td colspan=2>The simple answer to this question at your level is to go by damage ratio.&nbsp;&nbsp;Since you don't get a damage bonus in your primary hand at your level, speed doesn't enter into the equation, so you put the best weapon by ratio in your primary hand and the second best in your off-hand.<br><br>Complications - there is a 'damage cap' up to level 20, so a higher damage weapon is not necessarily better at level 17.  The 8.0 weight IBC is not exactly something that will keep you underweight.<br><br>My personal opinion?  Sell the IBC and the blackjack, and get another CoT and some gear.<br><br>&nbsp;<br>Keyeluke - <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415</a><br>Dripsy - <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=227922" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=227922</a></td></tr>
