	   <tr><td colspan=2>I found this out when I went to City of Mist with some guildmates and friends. I being a ranger had never really used harmony much, but the monk I was with had a hard time splitting the mobs so I went in and harmonied and lo and behold, I could see which mobs would agro as harmony only effected the mob within agro range mob I cast it on. I cast snare on the one that it didn't effect to check pathing and after that the monk was able to pull without any problems.&nbsp;&nbsp;So next time your in a new outdoor zone and have a hard time splitting pulls get a druid or ranger to cast harmony and see which mobs are tied together in agro.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Wed Jan  9 16:37:26 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br>Cannis 51st Ranger<br>Razer 50th Sk<br>Jeetkundo 20th Monk<br>Mikaraz 30th Warrior<br></td></tr>
